nd unreliable, instead seeing them as a resourceful population with considerable social and political resolve. Fontes's investigations into Northeastern life in São Miguel Paulista yield a fresh understanding of São Paulo's incredible and difficult growth while outlining how a marginalized population exercised its political agency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aInternal migrantszBrazil, Northeast. 0aMigrant laborzBrazilzSão Miguel PaulistaxHistory. 0aMigrant laborzBrazilzSão PauloxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh1 aWeinstein, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374299zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374299423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374299.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles